 BEIJING - President Cyril Ramaphosa has called on the Chinese communist party to work more closely with the ANC. Ramaphosa held a meeting to discuss bilateral relations with China on Sunday. READ: Ramaphosa begins investment drive in China The world’s second-biggest economy will be hosting the China-Africa summit starting on Monday and South Africa will co-chair that meeting. China is on a quest to become the world’s economic superpower and Africa will be its gateway into infrastructure development investment deals.